	dprr:hasNoteText "Senator in 44? A young follower of Cato (Plut. Cat. Min. 65.4, #) whom Brutus considered for a part in the conspiracy against Caesar, but decided against it (Plut. Brut. 12.3; cf. Cat. Min. 73.4). (TJC) See Wiseman, NM 263, no. 402.\n" .
